<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #333;
      }
      .header {
        background-color: #0a173b;
        color: #ffffff;
        padding: 20px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .header img {
        max-width: 150px;
        height: auto;
      }
      .header h1 {
        font-size: 24px;
        margin: 10px 0 0 0;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body
    style="
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
    "
  >
    <!-- Header -->
    <div
      class="header"
      style="
        background-color: #0a173b;
        color: #ffffff;
        padding: 15px;
        text-align: center;
        border-radius: 5px;
      "
    >
      <img
        src="https://va-claims-assets.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/VA_Claims_Main_Logo_Transparent_2_200px.png"
        alt="VA Claims Academy Logo"
        style="max-width: 100px; height: auto"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Email Body -->
    <div style="padding: 20px">
      <p style="font-size: 16px">
        Thank you for your purchase of additional letter drafts. Before we can
        write these for you we need some information about the conditions the
        letters are for.
      </p>

      <p style="font-size: 16px">
        Please go to your To-Dos page on our website and check under the
        <strong style="color: #0a173b"
          >'Complete your Detail Builder Questions'</strong
        >
        section (click or tap on it if it is not already open) to find links to
        the forms you can complete.
      </p>

      <p style="font-size: 16px">
        This will give us a good idea of what we need to know to write your
        drafts.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div
      style="
        margin-top: 20px;
        border-top: 1px solid #ccc;
        padding-top: 10px;
        font-size: 16px;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
      "
    >
      <p style="font-size: 16px">
        In your corner,<br />
        -VA Claims Academy Team
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
